CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 4, 1961, page 19, reads: "Honorable Mention - Beth-Sheba Chapter 25, Order Eastern Star. Prince Hall Affiliate, won honorable mention for its table of breads. Left to right, are: Mrs. Alma H. Rodgers, Mrs. Jennie Dobbins, Mrs. Josephine Walker, Worthy Matron, and Mrs. Grace Miles. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of four women, members of the Beth-Sheba Chapter 25, Order Eastern Star Prince Hall Affiliate, left to right: Alma H. Rodgers, Jennie Dobbins, Josephine Walker, and Grace Miles, standing behind table with baked goods and sign that reads "Bathsheba Chapter #25 Prince Hall Affiliation...," gathered for the Pittsburgh Council of the National Council of Negro Woman's Brotherhood Food Festival at the Hotel Penn Sheraton
